OL,3,CWales can stand on its own two feet,
OL,4,CPlaid leader says
OL,6,FThe leader of Plaid Cymru says his
OL,7,Fparty has a "clear sense of direction"
OL,8,Fahead of launching their manifesto in
OL,9,FWrexham.
OL,11,FRhun ap Iorwerth says the manifesto
OL,12,Fwould "define a Plaid Cymru
OL,13,FGovernment", which would be "rooted in
OL,14,Ffairness" and "driven by ambition".
OL,16,FPart of their announcement on Thursday
OL,17,F(9 April) outlined pledges to increase
OL,18,Fdevolved powers to Wales, including
OL,19,Fjustice and the Crown Estate, as well
OL,20,Fas taking steps towards greater powers
OL,21,Fover immigration in Wales.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/11
