OL,3,CWales can stand on its own two feet,
OL,4,CPlaid leader says
OL,6,FSpeaking after the manifesto launch,
OL,7,FPlaid Cymru leader Rhun ap Iorwerth
OL,8,Fsaid this year's election is an
OL,9,Fopportunity for change, standing in
OL,10,F"stark contrast to Labour's record of
OL,11,Fmanaged decline, and their refusal to
OL,12,Fmake a stand for the interests of our
OL,13,Fnation against Westminster's
OL,14,Findifference."
OL,16,FHe added, "And it is the key to
OL,17,Fstopping the threat of Reform, who
OL,18,Foffer no real solutions to the
OL,19,Fchallenges we face, dealing instead in
OL,20,Fempty soundbites and fanning the
OL,21,Fflames of division.
OL,26,@xD@KOU
